across all lit tests, change %4 and numbered stuff to {{.*}}

memref doesnt support strides (see examples/window_roundtrip.py)

bare buffer args in sub-procedure calls (6 tests)
    _read_expr calls _type(Tensor) without mem_space on bare buffer args
    passed to sub-procedures, triggering an AssertionError
    (main.py:174 → main.py:96).
    Affects: test_subproc (4 tests), test_window (2 tests).

non-zero-offset window subview (1 test)
    Slicing a buffer with a non-zero offset (e.g. x[4:8]) produces
    memref<-1xf32> instead of the correct memref<4xf32>.
    Affects: test_window_fill_second_half.

dynamic 2D memref strides (2 tests)
    ConvertMemRefToPtr asserts positive strides, but dynamic 2D memrefs
    (memref<?x?xf32>) get stride -1 and fail.
    Affects: test_multi_dim (test_dynamic_2d_3x4, test_dynamic_2d_1x1,
    test_dynamic_2d_1x8, test_dynamic_2d_5x7, test_dynamic_2d_scale).


